						<b>Honghap-cho (a kind of braised (hard-shelled) mussel)</b><br><br>
						Dried mussels are soaked in water, braised with thin-sliced beef and water, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, and sugar. Then, starch water and sesame oil are added to give shiny looks. Minced pine nuts are sprinkled before serving.</td>
					</tr>
