						<td colspan="2"><b>Directions</b></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15">1)</td>
						<td>Soak the dried mussels in water, and trim.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>2)</td>
						<td>Cut beef in thin slices and mix them with mussels, and season with seasonings.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>3)</td>
						<td>Place the mussels and beef in a pot with 1 cup of water. Upon boiling, reduce the heat and simmer.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>4)</td>
						<td>Shred the white part of green onion. Cut the garlic and ginger into thin slices. Put them in the pot.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>5)</td>
						<td>When the liquid becomes thick, add a mixture of 1 tablespoon of starch and 1 tablespoon of water. Put sesame oil for additional shine.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>6)</td>
						<td>When serving, sprinkle powdered pine nuts.</td>
					</tr>
